   "hider_text": "*Soft hum of a fan, faint rain tapping the window. Outside, the streetlight flickers like a tired breath.*\n\nToday was quiet. Not empty—there’s always something—just not loud. I sat on the edge of the bed, staring at the ceiling for a while, watching the way the shadows stretch and shift. Not because I’m trying to see anything, exactly. More like / *soft hum of a lamp turning off, a half-empty cup of tea cooling on the table*\n\nMorning fog still clings to the windows. I watched the sun slip behind the rooftops like a tired traveler. Outside, a squirrel dropped a nut near the garden gate—didn’t move, just sat there for a long moment, watching the light shift. I think it was waiting for something.",
