   "hider_text": "The salt in the air settles on the inside of my lungs like fine dust from a forgotten shelf. I can feel it in the corners of my mouth when I breathe too deeply. There’s a sound beneath the wind—low, rhythmic, like the slow pull of something vast dragging itself across stone.  \n\nI walk along a path that winds between two cliffs, where the ground is damp and slick",
